1
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:02,320
There must be some misunderstanding.

2
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:03,760
That's right.

3
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,130
Long time no see. You're Mrs. Song now.

4
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,680
I'm so envious.

5
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:10,200
We haven't seen each other for years.

6
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,330
I wanted to catch up.

7
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:13,760
Okay. You two carry on.

8
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:22,880
I've already let you off the hook.

9
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:23,760
What more do you want?

10
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,560
Since you also have a grudge against Yao Shengsheng,

11
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:27,000
why don't we work together?

12
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,080
My history with her is in the past.

13
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:31,080
I'm not interested in your affairs.

14
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:32,160
What if...

15
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,240
I could help you escape this life

16
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:36,300
where you're always beneath others?

17
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:38,200
I can also sponsor your sister

18
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,160
to finish her studies

19
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:40,289
and change her life.

20
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,400
You really are just like her.

21
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,600
No wonder Young Marshal Song asked me

22
00:01:50,039 --> 00:01:51,120
who you are.

23
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,410
You just threatened me with my sister.

24
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:58,759
How can I work with someone like you?

25
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,440
Consider this a deposit.

26
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:07,480
And thanks for not blowing my cover.

27
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,360
All right, go ahead.

28
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:12,360
What do you need my help with?

29
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:15,640
What was Song Huainan talking to that foreigner about just now?

30
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:18,400
I heard something about buying and selling land

31
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,730
and signing a contract.

32
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,880
Could I trouble you

33
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:27,010
to use Johnson's affection for you

34
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,000
to help me get that contract?

35
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:31,920
I know this is very dangerous.

36
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,410
I don't want to hide it from you.

37
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:41,000
Okay, I promise.

38
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:56,940
Outflank her. Cut her off.

39
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:02,280
They found out I stole the contract.

40
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,120
When can you take

41
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,440
me and my sister abroad?

42
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,100
Over there.

43
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:05,960
Run!

44
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,240
Stop! Don't run!

45
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,840
It's so late.

46
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,960
What brings the Ambassador here?

47
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,880
Bad news. The contract is missing.

48
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,140
That dancer named Rose

49
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,410
stole our contract.

50
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,000
Don't panic.

51
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,640
I'll send men to search the city right away.

52
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,079
Let's go.

53
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:31,680
We need to get back to the hotel.

54
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,880
My sister's things are still in my room.

55
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,200
I can't let them trace this to her.

56
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:35,680
No.

57
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,079
They must have surrounded the place by now.

58
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,000
It's too dangerous for you to go back.

59
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,240
I have to go back.

60
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:40,940
Don't move.

61
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,850
Hand over what you stole from the Ambassador.

62
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,050
She's my friend.

63
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,640
Do you have any proof she stole anything?

64
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,370
If not, you're slandering her.

65
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,840
You'd better step aside.

66
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,440
Or else,

67
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,800
I'll arrest you too.

68
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:57,140
You wouldn't dare.

69
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,170
Room 202, Mosang Hotel.

70
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,170
Don't forget your promise.

71
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:06,240
That's right. I stole it. So what?

72
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:09,160
Foreign devils running wild on our turf,

73
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,800
I just couldn't stand it.

74
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,200
Where is it?

75
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,490
Hand it over.

76
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,480
I already burned it.

77
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,800
You have a death wish.

78
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:31,600
Rose.

79
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:53,120
To Mosang Hotel.

80
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,480
We need to treat your wound immediately.

81
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,080
Let me see if

82
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,540
I have any spare medicine.

83
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,480
Do you have a lighter?

84
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,320
Come here.

85
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,250
Bear with it. This might hurt a little.

86
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:06,360
You are tough. Not making a sound.

87
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,240
I've suffered worse injuries.

88
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:12,680
How painful was that?

89
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,840
I almost lost my life.

90
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,330
I'm actually quite curious

91
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,800
about what you've been through.

92
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:26,980
Aren't you curious

93
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,440
why I had to steal this contract?

94
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:33,120
You'll tell me if you want to.

95
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:34,800
If you don't,

96
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,440
asking won't do any good.

97
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,840
This is a land transfer contract.

98
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,040
This is the secret deal between your brother and the foreigners.

99
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,240
Once this land is transferred to the foreigners,

100
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,840
Who could control them then?

101
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,600
My brother...

102
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,000
how could he?

103
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,240
Is this the place?

104
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:04,720
Yes.

105
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,080
This is where that dancer lives.

106
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,000
Room 202.

107
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,370
Go in and search.

108
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,040
Go.

109
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,860
Hurry up and go.

110
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,010
Can you manage by yourself?

111
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,260
Hurry up and go.

112
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,520
Shengsheng?

113
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,200
Why are you here?

114
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,880
Huainan.

115
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,640
Huainan.

116
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,020
You scared me to death.

117
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,600
I came to find Meigui, but she wasn't there.

118
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,800
I ran into two masked men.

119
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,760
They stabbed me.

120
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,050
What a coincidence.

121
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,600
But Ambassador Johnson just told me

122
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:05,200
that your friend Rose stole his contract,

123
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:08,740
and you just happened to come looking for her right now.

124
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,600
What?

125
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,960
Why would Rose steal the Ambassador's contract?

126
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:13,760
Exactly.

127
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,600
Why is she so interested in the contract?

128
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:21,860
Especially in the few days she was meeting with my wife.

129
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,920
Song Huainan, what do you mean?

130
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:27,800
Are you saying her stealing the contract has to do with me?

131
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,640
I don't even know what that is.

132
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,840
Do you know that by suspecting me like this,

133
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,679
I could lose my head if the Ambassador finds out?

134
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,960
Alright, no need to get so worked up.

135
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,220
I was just pointing out the coincidence.

136
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,640
Don't touch me.

137
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:47,040
I ran into bad people and got hurt.

138
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:51,000
My husband not only doesn't care about me,

139
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,400
but suspects me instead.

140
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:55,240
It's just that the timing of your injury is too coincidental.

141
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,680
That's why I couldn't help but be suspicious.

142
00:08:57,680 --> 00:09:00,640
But if your wound was really caused by an assassin,

143
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,840
then it's fine.

144
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,440
But if you were shot by Johnson's men,

145
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,700
then we have a problem.

146
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,960
The bullets in their guns are specially made.

147
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,020
They are poisoned.

148
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:13,880
Madam.

149
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,760
So you are the one I truly care about.

150
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,840
Search this place carefully.

151
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,280
Don't miss a single corner.

152
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,600
I'll take Madam back first.

153
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,130
Yes, sir.

154
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,240
Let's go.

155
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,800
You must have been frightened tonight.

156
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,040
Rest well for now.

157
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,360
When the military doctor arrives,

158
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,600
he'll treat you.

159
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,520
Alright, don't be angry anymore.

160
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,200
I'll go handle official business first.

161
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,560
I'll come see you later.

162
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,570
It really is poison.

163
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,720
I have to find a way to cover it up.

164
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:11,200
I can't let the military doctor find out.
